The Federal Executive Council (FEC) yesterday approved ten contracts for the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), amounting to about N3.7bn. The contracts were approved during the extraordinary FEC meeting, presided over by the Vice President Yemi Osinbajo at State House, Abuja. FCT minister, Mohammed Bello said that the contracts were approved to provide infrastructure to the city and satellite towns. He said the first contract was for the rehabilitation of failed walkways within the Wuse District of the Federal Capital City and that contract was awarded at the cost of N1.9bn. He said the second contract was for the preparation of the electricity master plan for Phase IV of the Federal Capital City at the cost of N189m. The minister said the third contract was for the design of infrastructure for what we called institution and research district which is in phase III of the Federal Capital City at N197m. The fourth, he said was engineering design of infrastructure for sector G and H in Phase III of the Federal Capital City awarded at the cost of N118.575m with a completion period of six months. “The next one is the contract for the construction of the School of Science at the permanent site of the FCT College of Education Zuba at the cost of N701m,” he said. FEC approves N272m for Abuja rail project FEC approves N378bn contracts FEC approves N9.2bn for model schools, ARV drugs, others Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin